<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910614-0153</DOCNO><DOCID>910614-0153.</DOCID><HL>   Cincinnati Microwave Loan Pact</HL><DATE>06/14/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B3</SO><CO>   CNMW</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>ELECTRICAL COMPONENTS AND EQUIPMENT (ELQ)</IN><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)OHIO (OH)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   CINCINNATI -- Cincinnati Microwave Inc. said it reached anagreement in principle with its lender to renew its creditfacility.   Cincinnati Microwave and its subsidiaries make and marketa variety of electronic products, including radar detectorsand home incarceration units for judicial-system use.</LP><TEXT>   The company's current revolving line of credit, which mustbe repaid by June 30, was $10 million, but had been capped at$6 million following an agreement between the lender and thecompany. Cincinnati Microwave currently owes $5.4 million onthe loan.   Under the new agreement, the loan won't have to be paidback by June 30. A new deadline has not yet been set.</TEXT></DOC>